1. Install native java. 
2. Configure Java environment variables on Linux. 
3. Create a folder and run the vim command to create java files in the “Source Code” folder. 
4. Compile java files using the javac command in multiple terminals.
javac CentralIndexingServerNode.java
javac PeerNode_1.java
javac PeerNode_2.java
javac PeerNode_3.java
javac PeerNode_4.java
5. Run the .class file in multiple terminals.
java CentralIndexingServerNode
java PeerNode_1
java PeerNode_2
java PeerNode_3
java PeerNode_4
